fix: mobile UX overhaul - settings accordion + responsive grid collapse

Settings page (SettingsClient.tsx):
- Replaced the broken 2-panel desktop layout (210px sidebar + content panel)
  with a full-width accordion. Each section (Profile, Appearance,
  Preferences, Notifications, Data & Privacy, Help & About) now has a
  tap-to-expand header showing icon + label + description + chevron.
- Multiple sections can be open simultaneously.
- Active section has primary-colored header with filled icon background.
- Works identically on mobile and desktop - no clutter, no misalignment.

Mobile CSS (globals.css):
- Collapsed all inline-grid layouts (div[style*="gridTemplateColumns"])
  to single column on screens <= 768px.
- Dashboard hero stats grid stays 3-across on mobile (compact enough).
- Hero stat values get smaller font size on mobile to prevent overflow.
- Cards get overflow:hidden and word-break:break-word.
- Added bottom padding to main-content equal to mobile nav bar height
  so the nav bar never covers page content.
- Toolbar flex rows wrap gracefully instead of overflowing.
- Tables get horizontal scroll within their container.
